title: Pasta
description: Frisklavet pasta
amount: 4 people
cook-time: 50 min
tags: pasta, easy to make

kitchenware:
    plastic wrap,
    rolling pin
    
ingredients:
    wheatflour [300 g],
    egg [3],
    salt+,
    water?+,
    extra wheatflour+

instructions:
    with(wheatflour, egg, salt, water):
        Put the [300 g] wheatflour on the table and make a cavity in the middle.
        Crack the [3] eggs in the cavity, and add salt.
        Start mixing the eggs into the wheatflour.
        If the dough becomes to dry, add water, and if it becomes to sticky add wheatflour.
        Knead the dough thoroughly.
        
    using(plastic wrap):
        After kneading, let the dough rest in plastic wrap for 30 minutes.
        yield: 
            dough  
              
    with(dough,extra wheatflour) using(kitchenroller):
        Add wheatflour to the table, and begin rolling out the dough thinly using a rolling pin.
        Start from the middle and work towards the edges.
        When the dough is the desired thickness, cut the dough into thin strips.
        Dust the thin strips with wheatflour, and roll the strips into a nest.

        yield:
            Pasta
    